{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2802","heading":"Definitions","label":"2802 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/ch16","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Committees” means the Committee on Ways and Means of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Finance of the Senate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “grape product” means grapes and any product (other than wine) made from grapes, including, but not limited to, raisins and grape juice, whether or not concentrated.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “major wine trading country” means any foreign country, or group of foreign countries, designated as such under .section 2803 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The phrase “nontariff barrier to (or other distortion of)”, in the context of trade in United States wine, includes any measure implemented by the government of a major wine trading country that either gives a competitive advantage to the wine industry of that country or restricts the importation of United States wine into that country.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Trade Representative” means the United States Trade Representative.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “United States wine” means wine produced within the customs territory of the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/7/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F7%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is made from grapes or other fruit;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/7/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F7%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"contains not less than 0.5 percent alcohol by volume and not more than 24 percent alcohol by volume, including all dilutions and mixtures thereof by whatever process produced; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/7/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t19/s2802/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft19%2Fs2802%2F7%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is for nonindustrial use.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
